SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1635
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR GREGORY (21).
7075S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 376.1190, RSMo, and to enact in lieu thereof two new sections relating to state
health plans.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 376.1190, RSMo, is repealed and two
2 new sections enacted in lieu thereof, to be known as sections
3 103.180 and 376.1190, to read as follows:
1 103.180. 1. Beginning January 1, 2027, pursuant to
2 the provisions of section 376.1190, the board of the
3 Missouri consolidated health care plan shall implement any
4 new health care benefit mandate enacted by the general
5 assembly. Such mandates shall include requirements for the
6 provision of specific health care services, specific
7 diseases, or for certain health care providers. Coverage of
8 a new health care benefit mandate under the Missouri
9 consolidated health care plan shall be effective for a
10 period of thirty-six consecutive months.
11 2. No later than July first of the year following the
12 second full calendar year of coverage for a new health care
13 benefit mandate and quarterly thereafter, the board of the
14 Missouri consolidated health care plan shall submit to the
15 president pro tempore of the senate, the speaker of the
16 house of representatives, and the director of the department
17 of commerce and insurance a report including data outlining
