18 the impact of the new health care benefit mandate. Such
19 data shall not include personal health information of any
20 enrollee and shall be given confidential treatment and not
21 be subject to subpoena, nor be made publicly available by
22 the director or any other person. The contents of the
23 report shall include, but not be limited to the following
24 data:
25 (1) Number of covered individuals utilizing the
26 benefit mandate;
27 (2) Overall cost to the plan to provide the services
28 required by the benefit mandate;
29 (3) The operational costs to the plan associated with
30 the implementation of the benefit mandate;
31 (4) The cost to provide the services required by the
32 benefit mandate on a per insured per month basis, and on the
33 basis of the total average cost of such coverage per insured
34 per month;
35 (5) A recommendation as to whether the new health care
36 benefit mandate should continue for the Missouri
37 consolidated health care plan, and whether the general
38 assembly should consider extending the applicability of the
39 new health care benefit mandate to health benefit plans
40 issued by health carriers pursuant to the provisions of
41 chapter 376. The department of commerce and insurance shall
42 provide assistance with the creation of this report.
43 3. No later than March first of the year following the
44 second full calendar year of coverage for a new health
45 benefit mandate, the director of the department of commerce
46 and insurance shall submit to the president pro tempore of
47 the senate and the speaker of the house of representatives a
48 final report outlining the impact of the new health care
49 benefit mandate on the Missouri consolidated health care

